DAMATURU – Following the declaration of 26th February 2022 for the conduct of the APC National Convention, the Caretaker committee met today at the party’s National Secretariat in Abuja to fine-tune its programmes ahead of the Convention. The meeting was chaired by the Governor of Yobe state and Chairman of the Caretaker Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee, Mai Mala Buni. The meeting centred on measures to ensure the successful conduct of the Convention. NSCDC Commandant Advocates Security Training For Pupils In Ondo Bayelsa Assembly Wants Probe Of Moribund State-Owned Motel The committee is committed to having a peaceful, successful and generally acceptable Convention. Details later…